The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorial optimization problems related to partial cubes, which are a type of graph. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves isometric embeddings, which are related to computational geometry, making cs.CG (Computational Geometry) another likely sub-category. The problem of covering vertices with zones involves partitioning the graph, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problems, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper involves some game theory concepts, which could place it under cs.GT (Game Theory).
